Table 2 shows final TTA scores after completion of all tasks across all clients on five Text Classification datasets.
We find the following observations:

(2) To demonstrate the effectiveness of Selective Inter-client Transfer (SIT) approach by limiting the number of foreign parameters (K=3𝐾3K=3 or 555) at local client while augment-learning, Table 2 shows a comparison between FedSeIT models (trained without and with SIT) and FedWeIT baseline.
For all the datasets, it is observed that the test scores of FedSeIT trained with SIT (K=3𝐾3K=3) are similar to FedSeIT trained without SIT (C=3𝐶3C=3) while having the same computational expense; however, reducing the number of parameters when the length of sequence of historical tasks grows at the clients.
